      <para>
       &productname; requires using Btrfs on its root partition and <xref linkend="" xrefstyle="template:snapshots"/>, the following sections focuses on
       characteristics of the file system type.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
On &productname;, the root partition is read-only. That means that many directories under
<filename>/</filename> are read-only too, except those mounted as subvolumes and
<filename>/etc</filename> that is writable by using the OverlayFS (see <xref linkend=""/>).
  </para>
  <para>
    The root partition can be modified only within a snapshot
    created by the <link xlink:href=""></link>&tr-up; command</link>.
  </para>
  
